title: Commission Regulation (EC) No 1166/95 of 23 May 1995 fixing the minimum selling prices for beef put up for sale under the invitation to tender referred to in Regulation (EC) No 1035/95
header:
COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 1166/95 of 23 May 1995 fixing the minimum selling  prices for beef put up for sale under the invitation to tender referred to in Regulation (EC) No  1035/95
THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
main_body: The minimum selling prices for beef for the invitation to tender held  in accordance with Regulation (EC) No 1035/95 for which the time limit for the submission of  tenders was 17 May 1995 are as set out in the Annex hereto.

The Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official  Journal of the European Communities.
This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all  Member States.
attachments:
Done at Brussels, 23 May 1995.
For the Commission Franz FISCHLER Member of the Commission
